   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The top section of the screen provides the operator with an overview of the entire batch
         plant that for monitoring and detection of problems. The image below explains the purpose
         of each of these buttons.</p>
      <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The latest incoming message appears at the top of the screen. Recent messages can be
            viewed using the buttons in the upper left corner, which are identified on the following
            page. The messages and alarms are explained in detail in SBS-OP-003 Alarm Message
            System.</p>
      </note>
      <p class="- topic/p ">
         <fig id="fig_d55_5xf_vcc" class="- topic/fig ">
            <title class="- topic/title ">Understanding the Overview Area on a Typical Screen</title>
            <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                   placement="break"
                   id="image_e55_5xf_vcc"
                   align="center"
                   class="- topic/image "/>
         </fig>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Four key operations have tabs in the Overview area at the top of the screen:  </p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">Silo Feeding</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Batch System </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Batch Cullet Weighing</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Maintenance </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To the right of each operation tab is a 5-segment group display that shows current messages
         for that operation. (Only three segments are currently used.) The messages include:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">A=Alarm violation of the alarm limit (white on red)</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">W=Warning violation of the warning limit (black on yellow)<image href="media/image3.jpg" placement="inline" class="- topic/image "/>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">S = Process control message </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">F = fault, error</li>
      </ul>
